<br>
I see now, Nessarose, why you have forsaken your own kind.  Is it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>he</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that is polluting your mind or is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>he</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> just part of a succession? No need to answer, really. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Noxxia’s eyes moved from Nessarose and slowly scanned the crowd. Her features had become hard and cold and she raised her voice enough so that all could hear.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Everyone take notice! – This is what happens when you are weak and turn against your own people! The Lightbringers will snatch you up! They will poison your mind – and certainly waste no time bedding you down!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Noxxia issued a maniacal laugh before returning her focus on Nessarose.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
You speak of Love as though you are an expert – are you trying to seduce us with your words and your actions? Do not bother, I find it revolting and see that you are but a victim and not an expert in any such way. <br>
<br>
The function of Love and those who promote it is to motivate everyone to accept things at face value.  Love at first sight? HA! A blatant disregard of oneself! That you would toss yourself to a stranger like a bone is tossed to a dog is indicative of Love.  Trust Love? Why, when any fool can love? Shintou is right when he said that Love is worthless.  It is worthless because it is diluted – and given away so freely. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Noxxia’s features had soften for a moment - the pitch of her voice was almost tender.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Do not think so ill of us Nessarose.  We are not without passions…not without attachments.  These feelings are reserved however, for those most deserving of it – those who work towards improving the species and driving the darkness forward. We reserve such emotions for those that recognize the natural hierarchy of the lands and have dedicated themselves to preserving it.  All others are not worthy of such regard. <br>
