<br>
For all his long years, loud mouthed zealots of hate and fear would preach, and what good has it done them? It has brought war to their lands..Wars that they tend to lose. It has brought poverty to their people...Though, he mused..Poverty does spawn more hate..So perhaps that is their goal? To be poor and spiteful?<br>
*shaking his head*<br>
It reminded him of that ruin he was born in called Cabilis. This Iksar had long ago stopped pondering these matters. For now he just leaned on his wall and watched...Ever ready to jump in front of Nessarose, should this knight tire of the sharp wit and words of the little rogue.<br>
<br>
Gozrath Sathir<br>
Overlord of Resolution <p>http://www.everydaymind.com/reso/gozrath.jpg </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=espanaye>Espanaye</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.oarbriar.net/images/MettlachLogo.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/29/03 12:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=123>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shake head.</span><hr size=1> Mettlach nods to the Iksar.  He smiles as he can almost read the Honored One's mind.  The grasping for power this one has seen as the loss of control.  To understand and to accept allows for the peaceful ways.  Perhaps wealth and power is not for everyone.  Thus why hurt one's pride in struggling for the unreachable.  Accept your circumstances and enjoy the time you have.  <br>
