<br>
*When Lady Noxxia is close enough she too speaks to Nessarose, only she speaks to Nessa of Nessa’s self. Nessarose snuggles a little closer to her Husband, Sir Mettlach and sips her Yukon Jack as she quietly listens to her talk.<br>
<br>
*As the Lady finishes speaking Nessarose empties her glass and signals to the bar keep for a refill. She sits quietly until he returns with the bottle she had given him to keep here for her, she tells him to leave the bottle and bring a couple more glasses. Then she looks straight into The Lady Noxxia eyes and begins speak to her.<br>
<br>
*”Lady Noxxia it is a shame that you see the way of life that I have chosen for myself and feel disgust. It is a shame, but I do not mind. You are not the first nor do I imagine you will be the last. It is your choices that make you feel so. And I can respect that. <br>
<br>
*If fighting to save Norrath from the destruction that the Greater Darkness would see done to her is to forsake my own kind, then it is what I must do. You should understand Milady I made this choice long before I had inclinations to explore the usefulness of men. I have much pride in Being Teir’Dal; it is not my kinsmen that I have forsaken but their need to hate. Hate serves only to distract us from, reaching our full potential.”<br>
<br>
* “You speak of my husband, Sir Mettlach as though he where no better than a light bringer. He is no more a light bringer than you or I.” Nessarose grins evilly at her husband. “While it might be true that this bard has polluted my mind, you can be sure the things that he… we have shared have nothing to do with the light.” Nessa smiles at Noxxia with a smile that hints of mischief. <br>
<br>
*”I do not claim to be an expert on love. The facets of love are so many that I will enjoy taking many more life times to explore them.” For a moment Nessarose’s eye seem almost clouded over as she is enveloped in some thought, then she sighs heavily as if to shake off something to painful to wish remembering. “In my lives I have been love’s victim and I have without intent brought pain to another through love. Yet these acts of love have only enriched who I am. Yes in the end there was great pain, but it is pain that reminds us we are alive. Now, many life times later I can look back on those relationships and thank the Great Maker for allowing me to share a small part of eternity with those souls.”<br>
<br>
*Nessarose takes a long sip from her glass, as she tries to put the words she wishes together “It is not love’s function to accept things at face value, on the contrary, to accept things at face value, is to see what is and accept that it is what you see. Love on the other hand asks you to have faith in what your heart tells you is the truth and put your trust in that faith. Even if it contradicts what you see.”<br>
<br>
*”Lady Noxxia, you said that any fool can love? I say the same can be said of hate, we need only look at Sir Shintou to see this to be true. Yet love can only be given freely, because its worth is priceless. You can not buy love; you can buy the vessel in which you wish sees you with love, but that does not guarentee that it will love you.&quot;<br>
<br>
*”Lady Noxxia, I do not think ill of anyone. With the exception of late, for this god called Bristlebane.” Nessarose’s eyes turn toward Shintou as she continues. “Although I must admit there are some that I pity. I pity anyone that would not embrace love for love’s sake. Those are one’s who’s live will only end in loneliness’.”<br>
<br>
*Nessarose smiles as the barkeep brings fresh glasses. She picks up the bottle of Yukon Jack and asks the lady. “Please come sit for a minute and have a drink with us. While I remind Sir Shintou of how he distorts my words and then we can continue this discussion.” Nessarose pour the liquid from the bottle into the fresh glass and offers it to Noxxia.<br>
<br>
*As Nessarose turns back to Shintou she sees an old friend in one of the taverns dark corners and ponders how she had not notice him when he had entered. She gives him a soft smile and turns to look at Shintou.<br>
<br>
 * “Forgive me these questions Sir Shintou. But, when did I speak of hatred coming out of love? Or when did I say that one needs love to hate? Of the later 2 questions I believe I asked ‘How can you say that you are even close to mastering hate if you do not understand love? Sir Shintou since we began this discussion you have resorted to putting words into my mouth and name calling. Neither of these validates your arguments. Except to say that your use of them is a good example of how hatred keeps you from reaching your potential. Are your arguments so weak that you must resort to name calling and putting words into my mouth?”’ <br>
 <br>
* “As for envy and jealously, they are just the emotions of people who do not see the abundance in their own lives.  Whether that lack of abundance is in love, material things and for you, it would seem power.” Nessarose begins to laugh again remembering Shintou spoke of his envy and hatred of those who are stronger than him. “How is it that you are so dependent on your God for power? Power is earned, by actions and seasons of endless hard work. To think that a god has given you, something that you have earned, that you given yourself through your experiences only shows how little you must believe in what you are. Earlier in this discussion you said you did not need your god to put you on a throne, yet you must wait for him to give you power?”<br>
<br>
* “To be exact Sir Shintou the opposite of hate is apathy. To feel an emotion as strong as hate…the only thing that could possibly be its opposite is apathy, to have no feelings for something at all. If you tolerate or accept something you are required acknowledging it. Acknowledging it requires in the end having some sort of feelings for it.”<br>
<br>
*   “While I can not say I approve of your abuse of love, in your own words Sir Shintou,  ‘You relished the pain you brought others ‘ it sounds to me in your own way love has brought even you joy, pleasure and some form of happiness. And while I can not speak for those ones that you cause to take their own lives, I can speak for my own soul. When the Lady Stargazer had been abandoned by her life’s love, she did just that, end her existence. And while her pain keep my soul at arms length with love for many life times, when I thought of her love mostly I remembered how happy she was while it was a part of her life. The thought of how happy she was, gave me the courage to allow love into my life. And if Sir Mettlach’s and my love ends tomorrow, then joy he has given me will have been worth the pain of its loss.”  <br>
<br>
*On that note Nessarose turned and smiled at her Husband. She then picked up the bottle of Yukon Jack and a fresh glass and filled it. Smiling she tells Sir Mettlach and the Lady Noxxia, “I will return in just a moment” and she turned and walked over to the Iskar who was listening from the corner.<br>
<br>
*Nessa smiled as she approached the Iskar. “Sir Gozrath it is good to see you in such good health. Although you look like you might be thirsty.” With that she handed him the glass of whiskey. “This is a strong, bold drink, for a strong, bold person such as yourself.” Then she leaned close to him and whispered softly, “Dear Gozrath when you grow tired of holding this old building's walls up we would welcome your company at the bar. That is to say if you would like.” Nessarose smiled softly and winked at Sir Gozrath, then returned to the bar and the on going discussion.<br>
<br>
* “So, Lady Noxxia where were we?”<br>
