<br>
That is an incorrect statement, for you can hate without loving at all. The two are not connected, and love is not needed in this world.<br>
<br>
I am dependant upon Innoruuk? Of course I am. We are his creations, no matter how much we hate it our only purpose in life is to serve his will. If you wish to take it further, Innoruuk is the Son of Hatred. Serve Innoruuk and you serve hatred.<br>
<br>
This potential you speak of is nothing but a lightbringer view on how we should be, meak, weak, accepting, upon our backs and legs spread so they can play out their little fantasities.<br>
<br>
I am sorry, but I carry a sword. I've had my fare share of lightbringer women, comming up to me pleading to be my slave, my pleasure toy to be used at my own command. I however carry a sword. I cut them apart from the living, every single one of them.<br>
<br>
That body of yours does not belong to you, it belongs to Innoruuk, and it should be put to a proper use in the service of the Father, not seeking some &quot;Potiential&quot;.<br>
<br>
But, I am just a ShadowKnight who refuses to die in the past with these views that I hold, of course. The &quot;Any Fool That can Hate&quot;. <br>
<br>
For Envy, you see it as seeing the lack in someones life? Perhaps that is true, but without that Envy most would settle and become, well.<br>
<br>
Become like you, the lightbringers. Happy and complasant with the way the world is, pleased with what they have. <br>
<br>
I am not pleased. I never will be, happyness is something I do not need nor desire. I wish them all to die, I wish war to be brought back to Norrath, for within war their is the purest of Hate. And within war, Darkness will hold Norrath once again. It is the only way to bring the world back to some sort of sanity.<br>
<br>
...But I tire aruging these things. And by no means am I in the business of killing people because they do what you do, namely sleeping with elves and defowling Innoruuk's Body that he granted you, and serving the lightbringers. What you do is your choice. I remind you that it was you who decided to speak out against my little message to the world about my city..<br>
<br>
I leave you to that pitiful wastrel of a man, I believe you call them Woodelves. I have lightbringers to slay, and wars to start..<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>With those final words, he turns to depart, leaving them be.. He did notice the Iksar Bodyguard.. and figured that the typical female, always calling in the protection, not that it was needed..<br>
<br>
He gave up converting people by sword after the incident with Dreyco... He exited the bar, returning to his home within the Necropolis.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=125476" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.studioeternity.com/EverquestFV/Shinsig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
