<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hatred by Envy.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nessarose>Nessarose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/6/03 11:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=126>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hatred, a funny thing.</span><hr size=1> *Nessarose turns to the Noxxia and smiles grimly as the barkeep pour Nessa three small drinks. &quot;I believe that I am begining to understand this emotion called hatred that Sir Shintou seemingly thrives upon.&quot;<br>
<br>
*Nessarose raises the first of the small shots the barkeep has poured for her. &quot;For the pups the she wolf may have left outside.&quot; with the toast said Nessarose down all three of the glasses, whincing slightly with the third shot. <br>
<br>
*Nessarose spoke one last time to Lady Noxxia. &quot;I believe for the first time in all my lives in Norrath I am truely feeling hatred. Strangely enough, it would seem it is directed at myself. It is truely a powerful thing this hatred.&quot; <br>
<br>
*Nessarose slips from her stool, bows to Lady Noxxia &quot;Forgive me Milady I have an undenyable urge to return to my home&quot; Before her husband returns from his conversation with his sisters, she pulls the shadows around herself. Nessarose quickly moves across the room, slipping out the door in the shadows behind Sir Shintou. <p>I am Nessarose Darksong, <br>
Daughter of Elpheba and Firero Okaimoko, children of the house of Ebon.<br>
The Witch of the Stolen Hearts, Daughters Nocturnae.<br>
And Forever the Loving Wife of Sir Mettlach Darksong.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=koliandrah>Koliandrah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/18/03 9:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=127>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No longer evil, just truly DARK.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>A female Teir'Dal entered the tavern, wearing a bloodred robe and carrying a skull-shaped scepter</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Claiming to look for free will as opposed as following a god's path is just a lie you are telling to yourself ever and ever.<br>
<br>
How can you imagine you came on Norrath if not by gods will ? Believing you can live out of gods paths and calling it free will is just a blasphemy.<br>
There were, are and always will be blasphemous people but it doesn't make their foolishness more valuable.<br>
<br>
Rejecting the gods ? Saying others are just their minions ? Aye, minions people are.<br>
That's why gods are gods and we are not.<br>
Are we supposed to follow their paths ? We are.<br>
Otherwise why gods would have placed the many races on Norrath if not to have their share of pawns ?<br>
<br>
Looking to escape from the gods tutelage is unnatural. That is the most unnatural thing to do if you need to find something unnatural in Norrath.<br>
<br>
We are not created to escape our creators will.<br>
Gods power your priest, shamans communicate with their gods through spirits, gods give power to the various arcane casters, they incarnate elements and concepts, from the Fire of Solusek to the Fear of Cazic Thule. Everything on Norrath is gods creation and will.<br>
<br>
You all who claim free will are using the gifts of gods. You're just able to use them without paying hommage. It's just lacking to recognize from whom your power come.<br>
<br>
Each god has its agenda, each god had and still has plans for Norrath.<br>
<br>
So there is no gray or twilight. There is no &quot;gray&quot; god, no &quot;twilight&quot; concept to follow which could allow you to escape the divine battles.<br>
Believing being in a gray, shady area, out of the dark and light battle is a lie you repeatedly tell to yourself.<br>
<br>
The acceptance of a Teir'Dal among good organization or a &quot;shady&quot; one at Neriak is just proving you can fool others residents of Norrath. It's not a proof &quot;twilight&quot; exists.<br>
<br>
What defines primary your role in the divine battle is the god you choose to follow. Race is the secondary aspect as every races trace its origin to gods so the divine battle.<br>
Teir'Dal are not supposed to choose their side, they are all tools of Innoruuk. Those who reject the role that were assigned to them at birth (otherwise why would they have born ?) are just traitors or weaklings.<br>
Claiming being a friend of darkness because you can come close or in a dark city just prove you're avoiding opposing darkness because of weak will.<br>
You fooled the guards, probably, you won't fool every inhabitants nor the gods.<br>
<br>
Being in the &quot;twilight&quot; is just being superficially friendly to both side of the war.<br>
Did you engage into human sacrifice and Fear rituals as much as you go curing people from Plague and make sheer display of kindness ?<br>
Probably, you just happy enough to say you're able to sell and buy in both Neriak and Kelethin. Trade is defining twilight maybe ?<br>
<br>
Protesting against the idea of being a tool, a soldier or a pawn of gods is like protesting because the sun rise and set every day. It's pointless. Norrath is the creation of gods, their battlefield and we are here to serve.<br>
Free will doesn't exist. Twilight doesn't exist. It's just an illusion for weaklings or cowards.<br>
<br>
Koliandrah, Necromancer of Neriak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elpheba>Elpheba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/24/03 1:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=128>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re; No longer evil, just truly DARK.</span><hr size=1> *Nessarose listen silently to the Lady Koliandrah speak, pondering to herself how many before her had stood in this tavern and spoke similar words. With all that the gods had put her through of late Nessarose could only feel contempt of these gods of which she spoke.<br>
<br>
*Once the newcomer finished her speech, Nessarose empty the last of the Yukon Jack from her glass and set it on the bar. With a glance she signaled the barkeep she wished a refill, and then she turned, slipped off her bar stool and looked confidently at the Teir’Dal.<br>
<br>
*“These gods of which you speak, I turned my back on them when I was born to this body. It was a gift to me by my parents who choose that I am agnostic, that I may choose my own path here on Norrath. I have found no god worthy of my homage. If someday I cross the path of a god worthy of worshiping, then and only then will I bow to a god.  While it is true that I am Teir’Dal, I owe nothing to the god call Innoruuk. I am a product of the Lady Elpheba and Sir Firero’s lust, no more, no less. And then they to abandoned me and my sister, at the whim of the house of Ebon.” <br>
<br>
*“This ‘Gray or Twilight’ of which you speak, you say that it does not exist. I ask, how did you come by this theory? If one who fights for good is light and one who fights for evil is of darkness, then those who sit in the middle must be a shades of gray. I gave up long ago trying to define if I was Light or Dark. I am Teir’Dal and because of this will never be seen by those of the light as light, but because I fight to defend Norrath against the darkness I will never be accepted by my own kind, therefore never truly dark. Where does that leave me? Somewhere in the ‘Gray’!” <br>
<br>
*“I serve only Norrath. The Lady Norrath has always provided for me. When I hungered or thirst she provided me nourishment. There is not a day that passes that she has not filled my eyes and soul with her beauties and wonderments. I have sworn my blade and my life to defending her from the greater darkness that has descended upon her. Norrath was here before the gods ever descended upon her and if those that fight as I, in her defense, succeed she will survive long afterwards. The Gods only use Norrath to play out their games, without a thought of defending or preserving her.”<br>
<br>
*“I do not deny that the gods created the forefathers of the greater and lesser races and placed them here on Norrath. That fact is burned in history and is done. The gods created them. Once created they bore children and those children bore children. These children where not created by the gods, they where created by a male and female, their parents.”<br>
<br>
*“If it is to be a traitor to turn my back on the gods then I shall embraces being one. I will hold to it and be proud. I Am a Traitor and Proud to be so! Do not think for a moment that it is that I am weak. Weak is to bow down to a god when that gods demands it. If you wish to be used by a god at his whim and then be forgotten when you are of no more use to them, all the time, you are praising him, this is your choice,  For me, all I have ever seen of the gods is the torment they have brought upon me and those I encounter. If I am to bow down to a god, that god is going to have to prove worthy of my homage not the other way around.”<br>
<br>
“Of late one of these gods, the one called Bristlebane began a toying with me. He pulled me to the sleeping realm on the day of my wedding to Sir Mettlach Darksong only moments after we had completed our vows only to return me to him later as a child. While I am sure that Bristlebane no doubt found great humor in this ‘gift’ he bestowed upon me, I can not. If this is his way to bring me to my knees to pay homage he is mistaken. It has taught me two things.”<br>
<br>
“One; that hatred is truly a powerful force that none of us are immune to. All he has done is by his whim is given me a hatred so powerful that I have swore to find the accursed lair to which he hides and slay him. And while I have no doubt I that now I would not succeed, I will go someday, until then this hatred will only spur me to increase my skills until I am certain of victory.”<br>
<br>
“The second beginning; it is true, we can not hide from the whims of the gods, whether it be Bristlebane, Innoruuk or that Goddess ‘whatever Marr’. If they decide that we will become their toy, then we are powerless to being used so. This does not mean that we have to play their game, what ever it is. Whether we cooperate or are dragged kicking and screaming, does not matter to them. For when they are done with us they will toss us aside for more entertaining pawns.”<br>
<br>
“I can see no use for a god that will use me but not hear my cries when I am in need. No I have seen no god in the gods of Norrath that listens to much less help his followers, unless it serves his own purpose.”<br>
<br>
“As for Walking through the cities of Norrath. There are few that I may not enter, the ones that I am welcome in, I am welcomed by all.” Nessarose chuckles for a moment, picks up her glass and takes a long drink, then continues. “Well perhaps not all. For it would seem that many a banker in Norrath finds my occupation a little unsettling. For reasons I can not fathom they prefer to kill a rogue rather than allow them access to their banks.” Nessarose shrugged and grins a bit mischievously. “To be sure this has nothing to do with whom I have killed or the god I may or may not pay homage to but rather it is an occupational hazard. One to which I have become accustom.” <br>
<br>
*Nessarose sighs deeply as she realizes that she grows weary. She turns back to the bar and slips back up on her stool. She takes another long drink from her glass, hoping to numb the pain standing has brought to her legs. All the time she stares at the ice and liquid left within. Wondering why she even bothers to speak, she knows that her words fall upon deaf ears, when spoken to those that choose to be pawns of the gods.<br>
 <p>Nessarose Darksong<br>
Witch of the Stolen Hearts.<br>
Loving Wife of Sir Mettlach Darksong.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=koliandrah>Koliandrah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/26/03 4:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=129>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re; No longer evil, just truly DARK.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Koliandrah heard the words but the exalted light in her eyes didn't flicker even a moment.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Gods are not supposed to prove they are worthy enough to be worshipped. They are gods.<br>
<br>
Newborn are not the 'product' of their parents, free from any kind of link to gods. Newborn exists because their race exist, because gods wanted that race exist.<br>
The link doesn't weaken with generations. Newborn are not remotely linked to gods, they are their creation.<br>
<br>
Are people expecting each newborn is the result of a divine intervention ? Are people expecting gods coming to each of them during their youth and say 'yes, you are my favored child' ?<br>
<br>
You just suppose you may refuse a god because he didn't pay a special visit for you, bringing gifts with him to please you. You just suppose because no god came as an avatar or sent you visions or anything else, none of them deserve your worship. You just have a high and misplaced opinion of your own value.<br>
<br>
You also seem pretty aware of what gods think about us, saying how we serve don't matter to them or that they will toss us aside for more entertaining pawns at their whims.<br>
How can you be so sure of gods thoughts ? Do they speak to you ?<br>
<br>
Are the ones serving gods forgotten ? Do they ever have a reward ? Divine powers and flowing magic are the rewards given. Secrets and knowledge are the rewards given.<br>
I just doubt every priest will say 'My god never rewarded me' be it in terms of powers, knowledge or enlightenment.<br>
You just prefer to imagine worshippers as disdained servitors to refuse reality. Gods are rewarding the ones who serve them. They are not forgotten.<br>
<br>
Your opinion about gods is also built on the theory they are childish. Gods 'play' with Norrath.<br>
You are supposing a mortal mindset to gods and try to find mortal motives. Gods are gods, they are not mortals. Believing you are able to discern their motives and being able to judge their actions is plain arrogance.<br>
Anyway, they don't play like children, they are battling. Refusing to acknowledge Norrath is theirs and a battlefield doesn't make the gods childish.<br>
You just prefer to think about them as children which makes you, in turn, wiser. You're wiser than a child no ? So you're wiser than gods.<br>
<br>
Gods are helping only the ones who serves their own purpose. They are. Why would they help their ennemies or people who refuse to pay them homage ?<br>
If you serve a god, you serve his own purpose, so you are helped.<br>
Gods are helping their followers. You just choose to ignore it and behave as if they don't.<br>
Maybe did you expect a personnal appearance of a god when one of his followers is in trouble ? An avatar sent ?<br>
A high opinion of his own value someone must have to expect such display of power.<br>
<br>
The fact 'twilight' or 'gray' attitude is followed doesn't mean it is valid.<br>
Someone sitting out of the divine conflict is not creating a 'gray divine area', he is just sitting.<br>
<br>
Your whole conception of godly existence is linked to the fact gods must do you favors. From your very birth to your daily life, you believe gods have to prove you they are worthy.<br>
You are reversing the relationship between gods and mortals.<br>
<br>
You are mortal. They are gods. Not the opposite.&quot;<br>
<br>
Koliandrah <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showMessageRange?topicID=182.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showMessageRange?topicID=182.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showMessageRange?topicID=182.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showMessageRange?topicID=182.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showMessageRange?topicID=182.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showMessageRange?topicID=182.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a> <b>7</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showPrevMessage?topicID=182.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showNextMessage?topicID=182.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=129><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.threadControl?topicID=182.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=182.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.unsubscribeUnregiste